@Node HDInstall " Maj-Jongg Full Documentation"

              @{b} H a r d   D i s k   I n s t a l l a t i o n @{ub}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

	To run Mah-Jongg from your Hard Drive.

            Boot your Amiga. Once WorkBench has loaded, insert the Mah-Jongg
        disk, then drag the disk icon onto the desired device or partition.

            You can now play the game straight from your Hard Disk.
        If you want to save space you can throw away the c: libs: devs:
        etc. from the drawer, as these are not needed anymore.

        You must keep: the Mah-Jongg program itself (never!)
                       the FONTS drawer and its contents
		       and the FILES drawer and its contents
    
	When running from Hard-Disk the disk operations are faster,
        and an additional -exit to workbench- item appears in the
        main menu.
@Endnode

